e. Scanning through the往路処理 steps again, the knowledge file correctly lists all three stages, so the documentation appears consistent with the source material. The exception handling looks consistent with the knowledge file — when errors occur in downstream or delegated handlers, they're passed through without additional processing. The section count warning appears to be a false positive since the source structure actually matches the three logical sections in the knowledge file, so I'll mark this as clean with no findings to report.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":17814,"cache_read_input_tokens":35069,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":17814,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c1502f03-e8cf-42bb-97c5-19f523a802ab","uuid":"a950cb2f-c271-4a7d-b5bf-5937364239f4"}
